sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J119347
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: eCDM8 expression + Theophylline riboswitch tetracycline resistance protein + GFP expression
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Low strength promoter (J119031) and a low strength C dog RBS (J119028) controlling expression of the eCDM8 gene (J100100). The clone also contains theophylline riboswitch D (Part J100065) and tetracycline resistance protein (Part J119140) and RFP expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brandon Grieshaber

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A low stregth promoter (J119030) and a low strength C.dog RBS (J119025) control expression of the eCDM8 gene (J100100). The clone also contains theophylline riboswitch D (Part J100065) and tetracycline resistance protein (Part J119140).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sachii Polpitiya Arachchige

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091131
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part produces GFP under the control of the lacIQ1 promoter. This promoter has a 15 bp deletion in comparison to the lacIQ promoter, which increases its binding affinity for RNA polymerase and reduces leaky transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Pallavi Penumetcha and Kelly Davis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pLacIQ1 promoter sequence came from the paper Glascock and Weickert 1998.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: See part K091112 for any design considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Pallavi Penumetcha
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is a modified version of the LacIQ promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J119304
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: eCDM8 expression with low promoter and low C dog RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A high promoter, J119031 with a high c.dog J119028, this combination is known as S05028. The eCDM8 gene (J100100) was then inserted into the S05028 vector creating a pSB1A8 plasmid with a high promoter, high c.dog, and the eCDM8 gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Todd Eckdahl, Claire Shinneman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Ribo-TetA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This device contains a synthetic riboswitch that can be used in E. coli. In the presence of theophylline, the transcription of the TetA gene occurs, but in the absence of theophylline, very little transcription takes place. This device contains a modified T5 promoter, which, in the absence of cymR, acts as a strong constitutive promoter. The ribosomal binding site is contained in the riboswitch.
This riboswitch is modified from riboswitch D as described in the paper by Topp et al.
References: Shana Topp, Colleen M. K. Reynoso, Jessica C. Seeliger, Ian S. Goldlust, Shawn K. Desai, Doroth??e Murat, Aimee Shen, Aaron W. Puri, Arash Komeili, Carolyn R. Bertozzi, June R. Scott, and Justin P. Gallivan. Synthetic Riboswitches That Induce Gene Expression in Diverse Bacterial Species. Applied and Environmental Microbiology, 76:23, 7881-7884. December 2010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sachith Dharmasena and Todd Eckdahl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Constructed using BsaI GGA of PCR products from J100065 and J31007.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BsaI sites were introduced into PCR products, but are not present in the final construct.
